<subSubSection id="ABE7655FBC4EFFDC51E9BD4AFF5DFA0B" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="E34236D4BC4EFFDC51E9BD4AFD9BFAA7" blockId="8.[151,1437,1089,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">
Type data: It is not clear how many females 
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4EFFDC53FDBD4AFCF8FBCF" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[643,837,1089,1115]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" refId="ref10183" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. 2. Roret, Paris, 680 pp." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier (1841)</bibRefCitation>
used to describe this species. One of those specimens bearing original Lepeletier’s label was found at 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4EFFDC53CEBD6EFCBDFBEB" box="[688,768,1125,1151]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHP</collectionCode>
and it was interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="876C4B25BC4EFFDC555ABD6EFB73FB14" author="Moure, J. S." box="[1060,1230,1125,1152]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref10360" refString="Moure, J. S. (1960 b) Notas sobre os tipos de abelhas do Brasil descritas por Perty em 1833 (Hymenoptera-Apoidea). Boletim da Universidade Federal do Parana, Zoologia, 1, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1960">Moure (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
as the “type”. According to the Article 74.6 of the 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4EFFDC5379BD82FDF5FB37" box="[519,584,1161,1187]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999) this can be treated as a valid 
<typeStatus id="3C468876BC4EFFDC52A2BD82FBFEFB37" box="[988,1091,1161,1187]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. The exemplar has the following data label: 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4EFFDC50CABDA6FDAEFB53" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[436,531,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysitis">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4EFFDC50CABDA6FDAEFB53" box="[436,531,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">chrysitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]\ 23 [handwritten]\ [circular label] du nord de la 
<superScript id="14889B9CBC4EFFDC5462BDA7FA9EFB2E" attach="left" box="[1308,1315,1196,1210]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Capite</superScript>
de 
<superScript id="14889B9CBC4EFFDC5420BDA7FADEFB2E" attach="left" box="[1374,1379,1196,1210]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">St</superScript>
Paul [handwritten]\ Type Lepelletier [handwritten]\ [red label] 
<typeStatus id="3C468876BC4EFFDC5264BDDAFC3FFB7F" box="[794,898,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Holotype</typeStatus>
[handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="24FD4D57BC4EFFDC5551BDDAFA9AFB7F" authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty" box="[1071,1319,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maerens">
<emphasis id="D189EAC6BC4EFFDC5551BDDAFB5BFB7F" box="[1071,1254,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">Centris maerens</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount id="F5FBFD5DBC4EFFDC5450BDDAFAFEFB7F" box="[1326,1347,1233,1259]" pageId="8" pageNumber="31" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
m. type vergl! [handwritten] det. Friese 1898 [printed]\ 
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4EFFDC53D2BDFEFCB9FA9B" box="[684,772,1269,1295]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHN</collectionCode>
, Paris EY25580 [data matrix code] [printed] (
<collectionCode id="85ECAE11BC4EFFDC5479BDFEFAE3FA9B" box="[1287,1374,1269,1295]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="8" pageNumber="31">MNHP</collectionCode>
). The type specimen is in good condition.
</paragraph>
